Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with managing users in wireless networks and proposes a dynamic channel borrowing scheme for interference declination, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the Quality of Service (QoS) and system capacity, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve multimedia applications in wireless networks, which can be categorized under multimedia. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed scheme involves controlling interference in wireless networks, which can be categorized under systems and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention security, interference management is a crucial aspect of secure wireless communication, which can be categorized under cryptography and security.
